inn1.comm: gentle outswinger to start the proceedings, Watson lets it go through to the keeper
full delivery on the middle, Watson gets forward, gets the bat around the front pad as he pushes the ball towards mid-on
length delivery straightening on the off and middle line, defended to the on side of the pitch
curves in a bit from around the off stump, Watson stays back to turn the short-of-length delivery to deep square-leg region
lands around the off stump line and moves away, short in length, dabbed down to third man
full in length and outside off, pushed out to cover
Watto brings up the first boundary of the day with a flick through midwicket. It was full and on the legs, inviting that shot actually and Watson obliged
around the off stump, straightens a touch, cut down to third man region
moves forward and across, almost walking out, to push out a length delivery to cover
leans forward to defend to mid-on
full delivery and hit straight to mid-off where Yuvraj makes a complete mess of it.
full in length, around middle, straightening, pushed out to Yuvraj
leans forward to defend a length delivery back down the pitch
bounces in towards middle stump, Marsh, who looked really rusty and out of touch in the previous game, stumbles out, tries to waft it across the line and is struck on the thigh pad
slower one, full and around the off, Marsh adjusts by rolling his wrists and gets the ball down to square-leg region
Risky single. It was mistimed towards Harbhajan at mid-off and Marsh called for the quick run. He makes it in time even as Harbhajan misses the stumps
short in length, straightening on the off stump line, punched back to PK
lands on a length on the middle and leg line, moves towards middle, deflected to midwicket
around the off stump line, defended to the off side
around the off stump line, pushed to left of Yuvraj at mid-off for a quick single
back of length around off stump line, Watson stays back to punch it to mid-off
on the middle stump line, back of length, clipped to right of short midwicket where Sehwag makes a lunging stop
And again Sehwag is in thick of action. It was a full delivery on the legs, whipped hard but straight to Sehwag who threatens a throw at the non-striker's end
bangs in a bouncer, high one, Watson shapes to pull but withdraws from the shot
full and down the leg side. Wide it is, says the ump Shavir Tarapore
short in length around the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
from round the stumps now to the left-handed Marsh who steers the full length delivery well to the right of Munaf at third man
bangs it in short and doesn't have the pace to hustle the batsman. Marsh accepts the gift and pulls it to square-leg boundary
from over the wicket now but slips it full and down the leg side, flicked to fine-leg region
slower one, around the off stump, full in length, tapped to the off side, one look at each other and off they go
on the middle stump line, whipped away neatly to right of mid-on where Harbhajan makes a tumbling stop
short in length, on the middle, turned to short midwicket
full delivery around the off stump, driven down to mid-on
on the middle and leg, whipped to Yuvraj at mid-on
in the zone outside off stump, tries to run it down to third man but is beaten
short in length, cut away hard but can't beat point
full in length, around the off stump, left alone ... Dhoni throws down the stumps at the striker's end and asks the umpire whether Marsh was outside the crease; Marsh had just about got back in time
short and wide, chopped straight to point. The bowling hasn't been great today but the batsmen have been conservative
full in length, outside off, steered to backward point
short and well outside off, cut down to left of backward point where Jadeja makes superb diving stop
Lovely gift there from Praveen. Full and outside leg stump and Watto rips it to square-leg boundary with a fierce flick shot
short in length, around the off stump, punched to Tendulkar at short cover
width offered outside off this time and Watson flashes it wide of backward point.  PK was trying to bowl the slower one, the leg cutter, but drifted it wide
stays back to work this one past square-leg
length delivery around the off stump line, defended out to cover
on that off stump line again, full in length, pushed back to Munaf
on the middle and leg, turned past short midwicket
length delivery, shaping away from the off stump, punched down to mid-off
slower one, around the off stump, pushed out to cover
shout for a catch behind but the bowler didn't go up. It was a length delivery that straightened outside off and Watson was beaten, trying for that cut down to third man
moves past the hips, past the attempted glance and Dhoni collects down the leg side
cutting in from outside off stump, turned to midwicket
moves in from outside off, Marsh nudges it close on the off side for a quick, but comfortably taken, single
Whack. Big Thumping pull. It was short in length and Watson pulls on the front foot and clears midwicket comfortably.
around the off stump line, guided down to PK at third man
slightly slower, on the middle and leg, Marsh doesn't connect with the intended flick and the ball rolls off the thigh to the on side
full in length just outside off stump, driven straight to mid-off
that nagging line and length continues; again on that off stump line from a length, pushed out to short cover
Watson latches on to the first mistake from Munaf. It was dragged short around off and again, Watson pulls from the front foot and clears wide mid-on region with ease
fuller in length and outside off, steered very fine and Harbhajan does really well to cut off a boundary with a dive at third-man region
Top shot! Lovely bit of stuff from Watson. It was a length delivery outside off but Watson knifed through the line' up and over the bowler. Flamboyant shot.
closer to the off stump, steered to backward point
lands on a length, on the middle and leg, moves in towards middle stump, pushed out back to the bowler

Superb hit this. It was the full delivery on the middle and leg and Watson leaned forward to flick it in the air over midwicket. Ala Carl Hooper. Well .. Hooper would have been more stylish but you get the drift
Wallop. 50 up for the aggressive Watson. Really fine knock. It was the short delivery from Nehra and Watson pulls it imperiously over midwicket boundary
Nehra moves from round the stumps now and hurls it in on the middle stump line, defended on the front foot
another short delivery, hmm Watson has pulled away most of the short ones on this pitch to the boundary but misses out this time as he doesn't quite connect properly
around the off stump line, Marsh tries to jab it away but misses it
tries the slower one and Watson appears to have been slightly beaten by the lack of the pace but goes through with the shot and scoops it well clear of mid-off
short in length, outside off, chopped down to third man
fullish, around the off stump, driven to mid-off
on the middle stump line, defended back to Munaf
Thrashed away. Overpitched around the off stump line and Marsh flays it in the air between the non-striker and mid-off

Catch it was the cry but it clears mid-on. It was the length delivery this time and Marsh tried to go through with the on-the-up shot but ended up dragging it in the air but it falls short of mid-on and turns away well to the left of the fielder
arm-ball, drifts in with the angle, strikes the pad but it was missing leg stump
goes right back to work this one to deep midwicket
turns in slightly from outside off, worked past square-leg
on the middle stump line, pushed out towards mid-on to Harbhajan and they rush across for the single
on the middle stump line, swept away for a single
goes right back and realises its an arm-ball and pushes it back to the bowler
flighted around off stump, driven wide of long-off for couple of runs
goes on the back foot to clip it wide of midwicket for a single
quicker one, flatter, around off stump line, Watson hurries back to defend
on the off and middle line, turned to short midwicket
fetches it from off stump and sweeps it to deep square-leg region where Gambhir mops up
on the off and middle line, going on almost straight, turned to left of short third man for a single
goes right back to tap it to square-leg
slower, on the middle stump line, Watson goes back to punch it to mid-on
the arm-ball skidding on the middle stump line, Watson went for the pull, was surprised by the skidding armer but manages to drag it past square-leg
pushes this one past the bowler for a single
drags it short and Marsh again opens up his stance and pulls this one - not the arm-ball- over wide mid-on region
on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
leans forward to work it to midwicket
flighted outside leg stump, swept to fine-leg region for couple of runs
goes back to punch it to long-off. 100 of the partnership up, the first of the series
dropped by Dhoni It was the off break turning away from the off stump, Marsh went for the cut but it caught the top edge and bounced into Dhoni's gloves and popped out of it.
again spinning away with bounce, Marsh misses another cut and Dhoni collects after juggling with it

almost holed out to long-off. It was the flighted delivery and he drove it towards long-off. Gambhir ran forward but realised it was going to drop short and he chose to back-pedal and stop the boundary
swept past square-leg for a single
fab cut. It was the short-of-length delivery turning away from Watson who rocks back, gets on top of the bounce and cuts it away to point boundary
the arm-ball on the middle and off line, pushed back to the bowler

He has almost made every short ball count. I can recall only short delivery from Nehra from round the stumps that he missed out on. This was another short of length delivery and Watson rocked back, opened his stance and hammered it over wide mid-on region
almost hits another boundary but Gambhir does a fine job at long-off. It was crashed to right of long-off, hard, but Gambhir manages to save the boundary
on the off and middle line, whipped through to deep midwicket
flighted around the off stump, pushed out to cover
sweeps from the middle stump to collect a single
quicker, on the off stump line, defended out to the on side
goes back to work it to deep midwicket
around the off stump, guided to short third man
leans forward to push to cover
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
outside off, skids away further, Yuvraj tries to late cut it but can't connect
slows up the pace, on the off stump line, swept away for a single
on the middle and leg, flat and quick, worked past square-leg
Bosh. Short and outside off, Marsh goes back, creates more room and time and flays it to cover boundary
turning, quicker on the middle and leg, swatted away past square-leg
flighted very  full outside off, Marsh curiously prefers to stay back and drive it to deep cover
on the middle and off line, Watson leans forward to defend
fuller, on the leg and middle, flicked to deep square-leg region where Jadeja makes the stop
slightly short, turns away from the off, cut down to deep point where Jadeja cleans up
short again, pulled away but Gambhir makes a tumbling stop at deep square-leg region to prevent the boundary
around the off stump, tries to late cut but just manages to stab it to the off side
slower, fuller, on the off and middle, turned to midwicket
slow and full again, just outside off, pushed back to the bowler
bit more air, full again, heaved away powerfully but it crashes into the right pad of Marsh at the other end!
slows up the pace again, short in length, Watson has to wait and wait and he mistimes the pull straight to short midwicket
this time connects with the pull but straight to the fielder in the deep
flat trajectory, turns in quickly, late cut to the left of short third man but Tendulkar makes a fine stop and the crowd roar
turns down the leg side, clips the pad and Dhoni 'appeals' for a catch but Shavir Tarapore doesn't fall for the old trick
flighted on middle stump line, leans forward to flick it to deep midwicket
from round the stumps, on the middle, swept to deep backward square-leg

Catch him was the cry but don't know who it was addressed to. It was the full deliver yon the middle, Watson swats it away uppishly but well clear of midwicket and the deep midwicket fielder moves to his left to cut it off
skips down the track and flicks to deep square-leg
moves down the track again and gets it down to long-on

Dropped by Yuvraj. He had intelligently slowed up the pace and tossed the ball across, Watson drove it straight in the air but hard and Yuvraj lunged to his right but couldn't hold on to the powerful hit
slow in the air again, on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
goes for the big heaving drive but is beaten by the lack of pace and ends up dragging it down to long-on
on the pads, clipped past square-leg for a single
really full in length, and again very curiously Marsh decides to stay back and is almost cleaned up but just about manages to stab it to short third man
on the off stump line, cut to backward point
when in doubt, sweep. Marsh picks up a single.
really full delivery, around off, pushed down to long-on
again stays back and moves away from the stumps and is almost bowled. But just about manages to edge the ball away from the middle stump
And back to that routine: Sweep shot for a single
jabbed away to the off side
short in length, pulled away to deep midwicket.
length delivery, straightening around the off stump, runs off the outer edge to third man
around 133.4 kmph, hits the deck short of length, bounces up, defended to the off side
full in length, around the off stump line, pushed down to covers
short in length, on that off stump line, tapped down to third man for a single
reaches his fifty with a little dab shot to covers. The crowd gives him a generous hand

Watson won't get his ton. Pity, considering how well he played today but that's that. Harbhajan has achieved the breakthrough. It was the loopy flighted delivery on the off stump line, Watson went for the big slog sweep but edged it high to deep midwicket
leans forward to defend to the off side
tries to swat it away but misses and will collect a leg bye
goes well back to defend to the on side
on the middle and off stump line, turned to short midwicket
around the off stump line, tapped to short third man
leans well forward to defend to cover
flighted slowly outside off, Ponting waits on the front foot before driving it well to the right of sweper cover
on the off stump line, leans forward to defend
loopy delivery on the off stump line, Ponting reaches out to drive to long-off

Dropped by Sehwag at short cover. Marsh skipped down the track, couldn't reach the pitch of the ball and hit his drive in the air to the right of Sehwag who dived but couldn't hold on to the low catch
shout for lbw as Marsh is struck on the pad, going for the sweep shot. But it struck him outside off stump and Tarapore makes the right decision
leans forward to push to point
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
quicker one, on the middle and off line, turned straight to midwicket where Raina fumbles!
manages to connect with his sweep shot this time and drags it down to fine-leg region
backs away from the stumps and cuts hard but Yuvraj intercepts at point
leans forward to drive through the off side
slows up the pace, around off stump, nudged out to point
slow again, drifts in gently on the off and middle line, defended on the front foot
flighted on a length, Ponting stretches well forward to drive to long-off
fuller, bit more quicker, driven to left of long-on where Munaf makes the stop
tossed up outside off, Ponting drives it down to sweeper cover
goes well back to push it past the non-striker , Jadeja tries to stop it with his boot and the ball ricochets away for couple of runs
on the off stump line, Ponting backs away to punch it to long-off
short delivery and Marsh cuts it hard towards deep cover-point region
flighted full outside off and Marsh swings it to left of long-on where Nehra tries to makes a tumbling stop but can't stop it cleanly
outside off stump, cut to left of point where Yuvraj makes a diving half-stop
short in length, on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
goes right back to work it back to the bowler
on the middle and leg, full and flat, turned past square-leg
slows up the pace, Ponting stretches forward to defend to cover
quicker but shorter, Ponting swats it down to fine-leg region
just outside off, forced off the back foot to deep cover
full and on the legs, flicked away to Praveen at deep backward square-leg
around the off stump line, squeezed out wide of backward point
outside off stump, full in length, punched through point
full in length, on the off and middle, turned to deep midwicket
short in length, straightening on the off stump line, squeezed out to cover
good delivery, kicks up from short of length, Ponting guides it to backward point
outside off stump, short in length, run down to third man
leans well forward to defend to the off side
flighted around off stump, stretches forward to defend
superbly struck. Yuvraj teased him with a well flighted slow delivery, Ponting took up the challenge and drove it inside-out over extra cover
on the middle stump line, worked past square-leg
quicker, on the pads, clipped away for a single
drops it shorter, pulled away wide of long-on for couple of runs
lovely delivery teasing in the off-stump channel, and Marsh is beaten trying to push at it
length delivery on the off stump line, defended back to the bowler
back of length, straightening on the off and middle line, jabbed to the on side
on the middle, fuller, flicked away for a single
fine delivery again, on the middle stump, straightening, trying for the lbw, Ponting checks his shot, brings the bat around the front pad to push the ball to the on side
short in length, bouncing on the off stump line, punched away to sweeper cover. Free hit coming up.
fires it almost yorker length outside off but the third man was brought up inside the circle for his delivery and Marsh squeezes it past the short third-man fielder for a four!
back of length straightening on the off stump line, guided to left of backward point where Jadeja makes a fine diving stop
Fine-leg is in the circle and Marsh tickles the full delivery on the middle and leg line to the boundary. Dhoni threw in a dive but couldn't stop the ball cleanly
switches the line to outside-off, dabbed down to third man
full in length, slanted across Ponting who edges it down to Munaf Patel at third man
full in length, on that off stump line, squeezed past backward point. 200 up for Aus
slower one, on the middle, turned away to Jadeja at backward point
the arm-ball on the off stump line, Marsh backs away to cut but can't clear short third man
shout for lbw but perhaps hit just outside off. It was on the off stump line, shapes to sweep and the ball rolls away to the on side.
Now Ponting goes for the sweep but can't beat short fine-leg
leans forward to drive to long-on
quickish arm-ball, dabbed just wide of short third man for a single
just over Ashish Nehra at short fine-leg. Ponting chose to play the paddle shot and ended up scooping the ball just over the jumping Nehra
Crack. Marsh leans forward to whip a full delivery on the leg and middle one to deep midwicket. He picked the slower one early and dispatched it without any fuss
length delivery on the off stump line, tapped to point for a single
length delivery on the middle, worked to midwicket
change of pace, slightly slower, full, pushed down to Tendulkar at long-on
on the middle and leg, Marsh walks across to try clip it to the on side, rolls of the thigh pad to leg side and Dhoni dives to make a half-stop
Top shot. Superb to watch. He moved forward down the track and flayed it on the up  to cover boundary.
Marsh goes down town. Loverly shot. He advanced down the track and lifted it superbly right over the bowler
quicker one, pushed through to long-off
goes for the big sweep but drags it to deep backward square-leg region
armer outside off stump, pushed to left of short third man where Nehra makes a complete mess of it. And Harbhajan tells him what he thinks of that effort
on the middle and off, bounces as it turns towards off, Marsh adjusts to defend
quicker, flatter, skids on, defended on the front foot
short in length, on the middle, pushed to midwicket. Dhoni is standing up to the stumps
slower one on the middle, Ponting backs away, tries to create room but can only push it straight to cover
Wallop. It was the short of length delivery drifting towards the leg stump and Ponting thumped it, pulling it over square-leg boundary
changes up the pace, slower one, Ponting is early with his shot and edges it to past short fine-leg
Done in by the slower one this time. It landed back of length on the middle, Ponting went for the pull but didn't pick the change of pace and the middle stump has been pegged back
oh lovely delivery, leg cutter, moves past the attempted defensive prod and goes to Dhoni
pushes it way outside off and Dhoni collects
around the off stump, steered to left of backward point where Jadeja makes a lunging attempt but can't cut it off
ooh fine delivery, bounces even as it cuts away from While who is beaten comprehensively
on the middle and leg,. fuller, flicked away past square-leg and Harbhajan fields
on the middle stump line, turned to Tendulkar at deep backward square-leg region
back of length, around the off stump, punched to right of Tendulkar
full in length, Marsh drives on the up, in the air, catch it was the cry, but Nehra, at long-on, is not quick to get across to his right and fails to cut it off
on the of stump line, punched past the diving bowler

the slower leg cutter, on the middle, clipped to deep square-leg and that's his hundred. He is delighted to say the least. The helmet comes off and he punches his bat in the air. The crowd applaud. White gets across to congratulate and his team-mates give him a standing ovation in the dressing room. And to think, he looked so rusty and out of touch in the last game. Fine fighting knock.
outside off stump, rushes on straight, Marsh tries to cut it but can't connect
on the middle, turned behind square-leg
the slower one, around off stump, cuts away, pushed out to extra cover
short in length, around off stump, punched to right of point
full in length, straightening on the middle, deflected to midwicket
Fabulous hit. He walked down the track and seemed to just flick it . It kept flying and ended up over midwicket boundary.
outside off stump, run down to third man
length delivery around off, carved towards PK at long-off
slightly slower, cuts away from the off stump, pushed out towards cover for a single
really full delivery, sliced straight to backward point where Jadeja fumbles.
Nehra goes for the yorker, ends up as  low full toss, driven to Gambhir at long-on
short in length, on the middle, worked wide of Sehwag at midwicket for a quick single
full and well outside off, Marsh swings it towards left of long-on, doesn't quite time as it was the slightly slower one but Marsh will collect two runs
Lovely shot. Great to watch. It was the length delivery, off cutter, and Marsh picked it, waited on the front foot and swung it cleanly over square-leg boundary

Marsh's fine innings comes to an end courtesy a good catch by Gambhir at long-on. Marsh had lofted the length delivery high towards long-on where Gambhir back-pedaled before lunging towards his right to take it. It was Marsh's maiden ODI hundred, surely many more to come. Well played boss.
leans forward to push towards Gambhir at long-off
'Terrific shot' says SMG on air and it was indeed. White went down on his knee to slog sweep it high over midwicket boundary
And again. Jadeja gifts it down leg side, on a length and White clears the front leg and slog sweeps it for another six
ah! he goes for yet another slog sweep but misses it and it rolls off the pad
on the middle stump line, full in length, turned to midwicket
goes right back but can only stab the full delivery to short midwicket
outside off stump, pushed to deep point for a single
yorker on the middle, scooped back to Nehra who misfields.
cuts in from just outside off, tapped to right of Munaf at third man
yorker on the middle stump line, jammed out through the on side; just a single
full in length, dragged towards deep midwicket where Harbhajan makes the stop
goes for the yorker again, low dipping full delivery, squeezed out to deep point
slower one, on the leg, Hussey tries to pull it away but misses
low full toss, dips outside off stump, dragged past PK who can only make a half-stop
walks down the track, goes for the big shot against the short-of-length delivery but mistimes it.Raina rushes in from long-on to cut it off
the slower one, from the back of hand almost, White lunges out, checks his shot and drags it to midwicket
from round the stumps, full one well outside off stump and Dhoni, standing up to the stumps,  can't collect that full toss cleanly
Thwack. Overpitched delivery well outside off and White lashes out at the width. He lifts it furiously over cover boundary.
slower one, punched down to Raina at long-off
Whack but straight to long-off. It was full and on the off, White drilled it down the ground
Hussey backs away and forces it wide of sweeper cover
And that is the record then, if the above trivia by the comms was correct. Hussey picks the slower one, clears the front leg and hammers it over square-leg boundary.
Oh what a shot. Superb skill. Hussey charged down the track, backing outside leg in the process, and crashes the length delivery inside-out over extra cover
full toss, swatted straight to Jadeja at long-off
yorker on the middle, dug out back to the bowler
moves outside leg stump, reaches out to square-drive a fulldelivery to deep point. 50 of the partnership up in 26 balls. Bravo!
short in length, pulled away towards deep midwicket
the slow bouncer, Hussey is forced to wait and he top-edges the hook straight on to the helmet grill in front of his tooth.Ouch
another slower one, a legcutter, flat-batted back to PK who does a skip and hop routine and the ball bounds off his knee
another slower one, this time the slow bouncer, and Hussey, walking across the stumps, can't connect with the pull
charges out, PK pushes it well outside off and it has been pushed out to cover
really full delivery, dragged down to long-on for a single
slower one, on the the off stump line, White goes hard into the shot, is too early with it, and the ball rolls to the off side
low full toss around off stump, hit down to long-off
yorker length on the middle, dug out through mid-on for a single
slightly slower, Hussey goes for the big swing across the line but can't connect
rushes down the track, picks the slower short-in-length delivery and wallops it way over midwicket boundary. Going going gone!
around 126 kmph short of length delivery on the leg stump line. Thank you, come again, says White who pulls it superbly over square-leg boundary.
around 129 kmph full delivery well outside off stump, White reaches out to drive to deep cover
the slower one, outside off, dabbed to Nehra at third man
Crash Bang Wallop. What a cameo from White. It was the slower one but slipping down the leg side and White pulls it to deep backward square-leg boundary. 50 up!
The white ball has been flying everywhere tonight. Full delivery outside off stump, White goes down on his knee and slices it to cover boundary.

Super catch by Tendulkar at sweeper cover and he throws the ball down on the ground in disgust. It was the full delivery well outside off, sliced again by White and Tendulkar rushes in and dives forward to take a neat catch. What a mammoth target set up by Australia. Super duper batting from them.

inn2.comm: low swinging full toss around off stump, square driven towards deep point region for couple of runs
well outside off stump, Sehwag chases after it and edges it down to third man
really full delivery around off stump, shapes away, squeezed out to backward point
lands outside off and veers away further, left alone
short in length and outside off, Tendulkar punches straight to cover. He would feel he has missed out on an opportunity to pick up a boundary there
back of length, on the off stump line, pushed to mid-on
whiplash! It was pushed across Sehwag who flashes it to the point boundary.
fuller, wide outside off stump, Sehwag has a swing and a miss
length delivery around off stump, Sehwag stays adjacent to the line and punches it on the up to very square point. Backward point too is in place
tapped toward extra cover for a single
well outside off stump, full, Tendulkar stretches across to guide it past backward point and third man fielder (Watson)  rushes across to make a sliding stop
around the off stump, defended to the off side
just outside off stump, punched out to the off side
slips down the leg side ...
drifts to the pads again, clipped away to deep backward square-leg where Bollinger stops
leans forward to punch the delivery curving away from the off stump to cover
short in length, outside off, punched to extra cover for a single
bangs in a bouncer and Sehwag, who is almost taking an off-stump guard against Hilfy, ducks
on the off and middle, bounces from short of length, tucked to fine-leg region
Tendulkar is on the middle stump guard and goes back to whip this back-of-length delivery from middle to long leg
lifting delivery on the middle stump line, Tendulkar stands on his toes to get the ball down to fine-leg region
on the off stump line, pushed towards mid-on for a single
leans forward to push the ball to right of mid-off and calls Sehwag for a quick single
climbs from short of length, on the middle and off, swatted away towards midwicket. Sehwag is lazy in getting back and had Marsh fired in a direct hit, he would have been in trouble
gets forward to push it to the off side
short in length, around the off and middle line, worked past square-leg
rotates the strike with a dab down to third man
Crowd roar thinking this would be the 17,000th run but Tendulkar can't beat square-leg
slower one, full and outside off, Tendulkar square drives, gets it past the diving short point but can't get it past the backward point fielder
the crowd will have to wait. Still short in length, cut away to backward point where Voges makes a fine diving stop
leans forward to push a length delivery outside off to extra cover

gets behind the line of a length delivery skidding on towards middle stump and clips it past square-leg. He crosses 17,000 runs and the crowd roar and roar. The banners are out. The noise is deafening. Sachin asks for a new bat.
leans across to mistime a drive to cover
back of length, around the off stump line, pushed towards mid-off and he scampers across for a quick single
he fetches the short of length delivery from around off stump and clips it past square-leg
Six over backward point. Sehwag moves outside leg stump and carves a short-of-length delivery over gully region
goes back and across and punches a short-of-length delivery to backward point. Free hit coming up.
moves outside leg and has a big swing but the yorker goes under the flashing blade and runs to the keeper
moves outside leg again but hits the back-of-length delivery straight to Ponting at short extra cover
up and over mid-off. It was a length delivery but Tendulkar punched on the up over the in field.
slower one, full delivery outside off, Tendulkar shuffled across, waited and went for the big off drive but edges it down to fine-leg region
dropped by Bollinger at fine-leg. What a miss. Sehwag walked across the sticks and pulled the short delivery to right of Bollinger who seemed to had it covered but ended up palming it behind him.
lifting delivery outside off, Sehwag tries to upper cut it but doesn't connect
slightly short in length, Sehwag goes for the pull but no wood on leather and the ball crashes into the back thigh
goes for the yorker but ends up as a low full toss and Sehwag whips it to the midwicket boundary
leans forward to push to mid-off
Classy pull shot. It was slightly short in length around the off stump, Tendulkar went back and across to pull it away to the square-leg boundary. Free hit coming up
moves outside leg, Bollinger fires it in full and well outside off but Tendulkar reaches out and slices it past backward point
from round the stumps, bounces it into the rib cage, Tendulkar stabs it behind square-leg
around the off stump, from short of length, Sehwag punches it to cover
he has flayed that. He moved outside leg and slashed the short-of-length delivery on the middle and leg to point boundary!
into the ribcage, tucked to fine-leg for a single and he will retain the strike
lifting delivery outside off, Sehwag lifts his left leg in the air as he clips the ball to short midwicket
moves outside leg and Hilfy fires across a bouncer in response; Sehwag tries to upper cut it but cant connect
bouncing into the hips, Sehwag shuffles in and shovels it clear of square-leg fielder
moves outside leg and whacks but can't pierce the off-side field.

Bollinger, who dropped Sehwag earlier, finds self-redemption. Good stuff from Hilfy who bowled a bouncer to force Sehwag topedge the pull behind short fine-leg; Bollinger ran back to collect a very good catch
outside off stump, punched away to off side
around the off stump, on a length, defended on the front foot
walks down the track and across as well to flick a full length delivery from middle stump down to fine-leg and Watson makes a sliding stop near the boundary
full in length outside off, square driven to point
charges down the track and tries to pull the short delivery but the ball flashes past the blade
around 135 kmph back-of-length delivery outside off stump, Gambhir goes hard into the square punch and fails to connect
full in length, just outside off stump, guided to backward point
around the off stump, Tendulkar punches it back to the bowler
leans forward to mistime the drive towards mid-off and collects a single
fullish delivery on the off and middle, flicked to midwicket where White misfields but the ball rolls to mid-on
bouncy delivery on the rib cage, tucked behind square-leg for a single
tries the slower one but Tendulkar picks it early and whips it over  midwicket
goes short again and Tendulkar goes back and across to pull it to left of deep square-leg fielder.
around the off stump line, dabbed for a single down to third man
on the middle and leg, turned to short midwicket ...
full delivery on the off and middle line, Tendulkar waits for it to arrive before wristing it between mid-on and midwicket
. It was the lifting delivery on the leg stump line, Tendulkar shuffled across and tucked it past the diving Manou ..
stays back to work it past square-leg for a single
leans forward to push the ball to cover
Tendulkar charges out like the good old-days but seemingly punches it straight to mid-off where Hilfenhaus makes a complete mess of it.
full in length outside off, Tendulkar is on the front foot, tries to square-drive on the up but no wood on leather
cuts in towards off and middle, punched back to Watson
Manou is standing up to the stumps now. Tendulkar shapes to paddle sweep before realising the ball is outside off and tries a late cut, Misses. Watson smiles.
it was short in length, pulled away to midwicket where White makes a tumbling stop
bouncing into middle and leg, tucked straight to short fine-leg
moves down the track, moving outside leg in the process and crashes it well to the right of mid-off for a fine boundary
bouncing delivery on the middle, Gambhir hops to defend it to the off side
Steered straight to third man. what a nice little moment for McKay. His first ODI wicket. It was the short delivery outside off, shoulder high, Gambhir upper cuts it straight to Hilfenhaus
outside off stump, rushes through the channel to beat Tendulkar's attempt to run it down to third man
And he connects this time. Skillful hit. It was a length delivery around the off stump, Tendulkar waits late before opening the bat-face and guiding it through vacant slip region
shuffles across to turn it down to fine leg
Full length delivery around off and Tendulkar goes for the big lofted drive down the ground ... too much bottom hand and he ends up slicing it over wide mid-off region
back of length, skids low outside off, Tendulkar tries to crouch and run it down to third man but doesn't' connect. Manou, standing up to the stumps, gathers.
leans forward to defend to the off side
reaches his fifty with a dab down to third man. 92nd ODI fifty.
on the middle and leg stump line, pushed down to the on side
on the middle and leg, whipped past square-leg
bangs it in short, good bounce on this track and Yuvraj stands up tall to push it down to short extra cover
full in length, straightening outside off stump, Tendulkar shuffles across, opens the bat-face, tries to run it down to vacant slip region but doesn't connect
shuffles across again and wrists a short-of-length delivery from around off stump to deep square-leg region
picks the slower one and crashes it over wide mid-on region. Superbly done.
outside off stump, tries to punch it to point but edges it to the on side
full and outside leg stump, turned to fine-leg .. would have been a wide had Tendulkar not connected with that
cuts in to the middle, flicked to long leg for a single
around the off stump line, runs off the inner edge past square-leg
leans forward to drive to long-on.
around the off and middle line, pushed back to Watson
good delivery, fullish, moving away late from Yuvraj who squeezes it off the  outer edge to third man
probing delivery again; it straightens on the off stump line, Tendulkar was initially thinking of whipping it across the line but since it straightened, he adjusted to jab it back to the bowler
leans forward to on drive for a single
flighted outside off stump, leans across to drive down to long-on

Thrash. It was the low full toss and Yuvraj has flayed it back over the umpire .. Hauritz bravely put his left hand out and he is in pain as the ball bursts through his fingers . That was hit very powerfully
floated on the leg stump line, tries to sweep it really fine, misses but will collect the leg bye
charges down the track and lifts it over to the cowcorner. He fetched it from outside off and found the wide midwicket boundary
gets across to turn this one past square-leg
full delivery, driven back to the bowler
moves down the track, doesn't reach the pitch of the ball and ends up pushing it to long-on
Ah! what a soft dismissal. It was a short-of-length delivery on the leg and middle line, Yuvraj tries to tuck it to square-leg for a single and lobs a dolly back to the delighted Watson who roars
in the zone outside off, left alone
tries to turn it to the midwicket region but edges it down the track
short in length, just outside off, defended to point
flighted outside off, stretches across to tap it wide of midwicket
full delivery, pushed towards Tendulkar and Hauritz makes a lunging stop
moves down the track, pushes the ball to the on side of the pitch and Hauritz makes a fine diving stop. Tendulkar had allowed it go between his legs but Hauritz dived behind SRT to stop it
stretches across to push to point
goes right back to tap it right of midwicket for a single
full in length on the off stump line and Tendulkar leans well forward to defend to cover. Watson continues with his fine probing economical spell
around the off stump line, on a length, pushed out to cover
Stunning hit. Tendulkar went back and across and pulled it high over midwicket boundary. Not quite like the famous pull against Caddick but a good short nevertheless
outside off stump, steered to third man
Now Dhoni picks up a single with a flashy punch to third man

advances down the track, Watson shortens the length but Tendulkar knives on the up, past the diving short extra-cover and Hilfy puts in a desperate dive near the ropes at cover boundary but can't cut it off
on the off stump line, driven down to long-on
turns past square-leg for a single. Tendulkar thinks about the second but Dhoni says no
stays back to push it into the gap on the off side. Extra cover and short third man in the circelt
Monster hit. This is the Old Sachin that we know. SRT waltzes down the track and lofts its superbly right over the bowler
Tendulkar has become Sachin again. The crowd roar. He danced down the track again and carved the flighted delivery over long-off
outside off, tries to late cut it but doesn't connect
on the middle and leg, turned wide of midwicket for a single
moves down the leg side, moves past the attempted glance .. wide ..
still from round the stumps, full in length outside off stump, steered to third man
full in length outside off stump, Dhoni edges the drive to midwicket
short in length, on the middle and leg, tapped to right of midwicket
on the middle stump. Tendulkar rolls his wrists to send the ball down to fine-leg.
around the off stump, slower, from over the wicket, defended to the off side
short in length, straightens outside off, Tendulkar tries to punch it to cover but edges it to short midwicket
on the middle and leg, short in length, turned to fine-leg

What a catch by Voges. Superb interception at point. It was short and wide, asking to be hit , and Dhoni carved it low to right of backward point where Voges makes a stunning diving catch. Tendulkar stands alone.
around the off stump, steered to backward point
slips it down the leg side .. wide
dropped by White at lone slip It was the length delivery outside off and Raina went for the cut; it flew off the edge and climbed over White who jumped but couldn't hold on
gets it through the off side for a single
around the off stump line, tapped close to the off side
short in length, angling away, dabbed to third man
pushed past point
on the pads, tucked to fine-leg region for a single
short and wide, cut away to deep cover
leans forward to punch on the up and the ball squirts down to wide third man
on the middle and leg, turned to the on side.
full in length, around off stump, he wanted to lift it over mid-off but it sliced away over cover

shuffles across to glance a short-of-length delivery to fine-leg region. Tendulkar turns for the second, Raina says no, and Tendulkar slips but recovers to get back in time. The throw had gone to the striker's end
bouncing short-of-length delivery on the leg stump line, shoveled to midwicket
full delivery, Tendulkar stays back to push it down to long-on
short in length, around off stump, opens the bat-face to get the ball down to third man
Flamboyant hit over midwicket. He has whacked that. It was a length delivery on the middle and off line and Raina swung it over midwicket
short and wide and Raina crashes it to the point boundary. Crack of doom. He lashed out at that
on the middle and off line, taps to cover point for a single that would bring Sachin on strike. The crowd love that.
beaten outside off. It was the short-of-length delivery in the corridor, Sachin thought he will run it down to third man for a single but the ball whooshes past the blade

Gets it this time. To the same third man. This is his 45th ODI hundred and 9th  against Australia. The Tendulkar salute comes out and the crowd, as you would expect, clear their throat. What a fine innings this has been.
leans forward to punch through cover
short in length, outside off stump, mistimes his cut past point
leans forward to drive to left of short extra cover where Ponting makes a super diving stop and what;s more releases the throw quickly
moves down the track, backs outside leg, and hits to long-off. He wanted to go inside-out well clear of that fielder but got too close to the ball
leans forward to push to cover
gets forward, tries to whip the delivery dipping in front of the middle stump but edges it to the off side
well outside off stump, Raina reaches out, tries to cut but doesn't connect
goes right back to clip it to left of short fine-leg fielder
on the middle stump line, tapped to the on side
on the off stump line, punched straight to short extra cover
backs away to push it to covers for a single
moves down the track, turns it to short fine-leg and Raina rushes for the risky run and dives to get back inside his crease
on the middle and off, defended to the off side
charges down the track, goes for the big drive but the ball drifts in to run off the inner half of the bat to midwicket
Raina goes down the track and drags the intended big hit to left of short midwicket where Ponting makes a super stop and again, throws it quickly back to the stumps
slows up the pace, dabbed to short third man
moves down the track and lofts it to Hilfenhaus at sweeper cover ..
Crash. Bang. Wallop. He charged down  the track and lifted it over long-on
goes down the track even as he moves outside leg, Voges fires it in to the leg side, following him, and its pushed down to long-on
walks down the track and whips it to deep midwicket
Dropped by Ponting at short extra cover. Raina moved down the track and lifted it over Ponting who leaped , stretched his hand out but palmed it over
The mad dash continues. Frenetic hitting. Raina rushes down the track and crashes it over long-on
quicker, flatter, defended to the on side
goes right back to work it behind square-leg for a single
fetches the ball from around off and paddles it to right of short fine-leg where Bollinger makes a tumbling stop
goes down the track again and has another big heave but it bounces once before reaching long-on.
couple of steps down the track and drives to Ponting at short extra cover
moves well back to clip it behind square-leg

Top shot. He backed outside leg even as he went down the track, Voges bowled very well actually, followed him to cramp him but Tendulkar got the bottom-hand working over time and lifted it over wide midwicket
hit down to long-off for a single
reaches across to drive powerfully but straight to sweeper cover
on the pads, turned wide of midwicket
Edged to left of Manou. It was short and outside off, Tendulkar tried to force it through covers but it runs to left of Manou  who gets a bad bounce just as he pushes his left hand at the ball
leans forward to push the ball back down the track
short in length, Tendulkar shuffles across to clip from the middle stump line past square-leg
sharp bouncer, high and climbing over Raina who manages to get under the ball
charged out, moves outside leg in the process, Hilfy slips in a slower one and Raina adjusts to run it down to third man
around the off stump line, Tendulkar nudges it to third man
Full in length, skids on towards leg stump, beats the flick and hits the pad. Was there some inside edge there and probably missing leg stump
leans forward to push to the off side
leans forward to drive past the bowler
moves outside leg and cuts straight to point. One run from 4 balls
full delivery, on the middle, driven to long-on

Topshot. Again, so skillful. It was short in length outside off, there were two fielders there - short third man and a very fine backward point but Tendulkar opens the bat-face and finds that very gap superbly
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket region for a single
on the leg stump line, Tendulkar shuffles, tries to clip it away and it bounds off the pad. It pitched well outside leg stump.
full in length, around the off stump, tapped to cover for a single
high bouncer and it climbs well over Tendulkar. Wide.
lands around the leg stump, moves in, clipped to deep square-leg

Raina is almost run out short in length, pushed to cover point and he rushes across for a single. Voges with the throw but Raina tries to dive in. But if it were a direct hit, forget that dive, Raina would have been a goner!
outside off stump, angling away, flashed to third man
full in length, just outside off, Tendulkar gets across to defend
slightly short in length, Tendulkar goes for the pull but mistimes it towards Ponting at short midwicket
bangs in a bouncer and Tendulkar ducks. One for the over, says Tarapore.
back of length, around the off stump line, Tendulkar punches it to point

short in length outside off, Tendulkar gets back and across and goes for the big pull but edges it to his body and the ball rolls to the on side. Raina calls Tendulkar for a quick single and both get across in time
slower one, length delivery on the middle, Raina backs away, opens the bat-face but slices it straight to backward point.
really full delivery around off, punched down to sweeper cover
its a short delivery, Raina hops to push it to midwicket and shouts out NO as he sees Tendulkar advancing down the track
good stuff from Bollinger; yorker length on the middle stump. Good stuff from Raina; calmly pushes it through mid-on
short in length, moving away from Tendulkar who tries to fetch it from around off stump and attempts to tuck it to on side for a single but ends up pushing it back to the bowler
slower, around off stump, Tendulkar waits on the front foot before pushing it past the bowler
length delivery skidding in towards off and middle, Raina leans forward to play a compact defensive stroke
full delivery outside off, TEndulkar tries to sweep it and misses it. Oohs and aahs from the bowler and the keeper

almost caught by Hussey, It was a length delivery on the off stump line and Tendulkar punched on the up and over Hussey who tries to grab it but it bursts through. Very difficult chance. a half-chance
turns this one past square-leg
pushes it down the ground
Tendulkar is predetermining that sweep shot but again, doesn't pull it off. He tries to fetch it from well outside off and edges it to his body. Perhaps , a paddle shot would be better

Ah! he collects a four from a paddle shot. It was on a length, around the middle and perhaps tilting in towards middle and leg, Tendulkar went down on his knee, waited before paddling it between the keeper and short fine-leg fielder
gets forward to push it to midwicket
stays back to wrist a length delivery drifting to his pads to fine-leg region
edged over vacant slip region. Tendulkar charged down the track, moved outside leg, and tried to lift it over the bowler but got a thick edge
bangs in a bouncer just outside off, Tendulkar was initially thinking of leaving but decides to go for his upper cut over slip region but couldn't connect
hops to get on top of the bouncing delivery and turns it past square-leg
Violent fore-hand cross court. It was the short-of-length delivery around off, Raina flat-bats it to long-off boundary
full delivery outside off, driven down to long-off
length delivery around off stump, forced away to long-on
Thrash! He moved outside leg stump and whacked the short-of-length delivery through extra cover. 150 up for SRT. The crowd cheer long.
leans forward to drive to cover
Whiplash! It was length delivery outside off and Tendulkar opens the bat-face and lashes it wide of backward point
gets forward to drive to left of long-on and Raina pushes him hard to come back for the second run

run out missed Raina had turned the full toss straight to White at midwicket and Tendulkar had moved too far down the track. Had white hit the stumps, Tendulkar would not even be in the same frame. Tension. Pressure
Nerves showing there. Now Raina pushes to backward point and wants a single. Its' not there and he just about gets back in time but would take the over throw
Classy stylish flick. He shuffles in, waits for the full in swinging delivery to come in on the middle and leg line before he flicks it away to the boundary
full in length, outside off stump, Tendulkar stumbles forward to mistime it back to the bowler
high harmless bouncer outside off .. Wide. Crowd love it.
yummy inside-out off drive! It was the full pitched delivery around off stump and Tendulkar creams it well to the left of mid-off
short in length, bouncing outside off, stabbed off the shoulder of the bat past backward point
leans well forward to push-drive it through mid-on .. some hesitation between the two but they get across. Tendulkar walks across to have a talk with Raina
mistimes the drive to the on side, Tendulkar wants a single but has to get back as the bowler makes a desperate stop

50 up in style. Raina punches his gloves in the air, the crowd applaud. It was the length delivery around off stump, he leaned forward to swing it high over midwicket boundary. Camera pans to Ponting who sinks down to his knees as he stares ahead
outside off stump, punched to point
full pitched down the leg side and Raina makes sure he gets bat to ball and ensures he has flicked it well clear of the short fine-leg fielder
moves forward to drive down to long-off
length delivery around off stump line, pushed out to short extra cover
on the middle stump line, Raina opens the bat-face, steers the ball to backward point
And then they were five. It was the short delivery, Raina top-edges the pull and Manou runs back to take a very good tumbling catch. Fine supporting act comes to an end.
short in length, just outside off stump, run down to third man. 300 up as well,.
cuts in from a length, on the middle stump line, defended to the on side

Double strike by Watson and Australia roar back in style. The famed Australianism; they refuse to fade away. It was the length delivery straightening outside off, Harbhajan tries to wrist to the point/ thirdman region but gets a feather nick. Tendulkar is still there and India's hopes rest on his big broad bat.
full delivery on the middle, trying for the lbw, flicked to midwicket
short in length, cuts in to middle and perhaps tilting in to middle and leg, Tendulkar shuffles across to whip to deep backward square-leg region
the high full toss, slipped out of his hand and it goes just below chest-high and Tendulkar defends.
length delivery on the off stump line, defended to cover
short in length around off stump, Tendulkar gets across to punch it to sweeper cover
bounces into the ribcage, Jadeja twists his body and swats the ball down to fine-leg region
length delivery outside off, timed sweetly but straight to backward point
just outside the off stump, rushes on straight, jadeja is beaten, trying to run it down to third man
short in length and outside off, punched away to deep backward point
full toss, on the middle and off, square driven to deep point region
moves outside leg stump, Bollinger tries to follow him and Tendulkar slashes it down to third man

Run out missed  Again Tendukar survives. It was Ponting at cover who intercepted the drive and fired in a throw at the non-striker's end. Tendulkar had backed too far down the track and had given up; he was nowhere in picture
short in length, flat-batted past the bowler for a single
on the pads, rolls away off the pad to the off side ... Tendulkar calls him over for a single and Jadeja rushes across to make it in time.
lovely slower one, on the middle and leg, Tendulkar was pressing forward, waited on the front foot before tapping it to backward point region
Shot! he has hammered that. It was the length delivery around the off stump and Jadeja crashes inside-out, in the air, well to the right of mid-off
banged in short on the middle stump line, Jadeja pulls it over midwicket for couple of runs.
lifting delivery outside off, Jadjea was shaping to force it but pulls away from the ball after seeing the extra bounce
oh .. he bowls it full and outside leg and Jadeja misses the flick and Manou makes a good diving take ..
low dipping full toss, hit down to long-on for a single
Thwack! It was short of length delivery outside off and Jadeja square-cuts it superbly to point boundary. Tendulkar punches Jadeja's gloves
Full and outside off, Jadeja goes for the cover drive but gets a lucky fat edgee that takes the ball through the vacant slip region
in the zone outside off, tries to dab it to third man but misses
short in length, on the middle and leg, turned towards midwicket for a single
almost a yorker, short of blockhole, flicked away from the middle stump line
full in length, moves in towards the pad, inside edge, runs just past square-leg .. no one there and Jadeja runs really hard and scampers home for the second run. The crowd love that effort.

Sachin is gone, the crowd go silent before giving him a standing ovation. Tendulkar moved across the stumps, McKay, known for his slower one, bowled one from back of the hand and it bounced. Tendulkar tries to paddle-scoop it over short fine-leg but alas for him it goes straight up and the fielder takes a dolly. But spare a thought for Sachin. What a great knock this has been. He has entertained one and all with a fabulous innings and taken India close. Will the rest do the job or will it be Chennai 1999 all over again? Can Australia go for the kill?
goes for the pull, misses but will collect a leg bye
Drama. First a yorker then almost a run out. It was dug out to the off side, McKay rushes to his left, grabs the ball and fires in a throw at the striker's end., PK dives but the ball misses

It looks like Chennai 1999 here folks. Exit SRT and the collapse begins. Jadeja is run out He was run out last game under similar pressure condition and he has succumbed again. It was pushed straight to cover and Jadjea sets for a non-existent single. PK does the obvious thing: sends him back but too late. The throw comes in to the bowler who takes out the stumps. Australian fielders erupt in joy

low full toss outside off stump, lashed out to third man and oh dear! almost another run out. Pressure. There was a slight fumble at third man and PK wants the second but Nehra, wisely, sends him back.

More drama Another run out almost but it has been a superb over ... lovely slower one, bouncing away, runs off the edge to point and again, almost another run out The throw comes in and Nehra is just short of the crease but it's not a direct hit. Panic has set in.

And then they were two. Australia rock on. What a wonderful fighting performance from Oz. IT was the full delivery and Nehra chips it straight to long-on! The crowd fall silent as Nehra trudges off. In the middle, a cloud of yellow are in charge and celebrating in the huddle.
OMG! PK has hit a six over long-off! He moved outside leg stump and biffed it high over long-off. The stunned crowd suddenly find their voice.
length delivery on the middle stump, steered to backward point and PK screams out NOOOO and Munaf, who had moved down the track, gets back in time
moves outside leg, Bollinger fires in a yorker and it just about misses the off stump ... ooh .. Bollingger stares down the pitch
backs outside leg stump, Bollinger follows him and it bounds off his pad to third man. Munaf has one ball left to face. Can Bollinger take him out? Can Munaf hang on?

from round the stumps, back of length, skids in just outside off, Munaf stays adjacent to the line and steers it to third man. He will be on strike. Hope floats for Australia. They will reckon one good ball or even a nervous run out
really full delivery and Munaf very calmly steers it to third man. Crowd go mad.
goes for the big hit and drags it to right of midwicket. He was aiming for the long-on there. He is not happy with himself. Munaf back on strike

oh what nervous drama here. Tension killing everyone. IT was the length delivery that moved past Munaf to the keeper. But PK was charging down the track. Manou under-arms the throw but misses the stumps

Hauritz you beauty! Hauritz with the deadly throw and PK is run out. It was referred to third umpire,.  It was driven hard to left of long-off and they go for the second run. Hauritz fires it to the striker's end where PK is scampering hard. He reaches out with his bat and tries to slide it in. Perhaps, he should have tried to dive in. The ball rushes past him, reaches Manou who breaks the stumps with the bat just outside the line! Australianism prevails.  They refused to fade away, refused to give an inch and India, despite a great knock from Sachin, fall short. Just like that last dismissal. What a game. Immense fun.
